##You stay home and watch short videos, and the video bloggers are running out of food

Weixin Signal Wowjiemian

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

Photo: UNSPLASH

Reporter: Zheng Jieyao Editor: Wen Shuqi

The number of people watching the video increased, but the people making the video didn't get any better.

Xiaojiu hesitated and decided to explain the situation to her fans. He sat in front of his computer in his pajamas and turned on his camera.

"Guys, we've been at home for over a week because of the outbreak, and now I've got three pre-festival videos in my hands, and if it doesn't abate by the end of February, we may really have to shut down. "

Three years ago, Xiao Jiu and friends together to create the "manhole cover team" this Ip, to the Beijing area of food exploration shop as the main content. Today, the platform has more than 3 million followers.

Xiao Jiu used to be most proud of his achievements. But right now, with this outbreak, it's all about safety. "What can be done? We can only hope that the outbreak can be effectively controlled by the end of February. "

###We're running low on chips

This Spring Festival, an epidemic, disrupted the update rhythm of many short video creators.

Food Blogger Mi Zijun originally planned to broadcast more than a dozen taiwan-themed food programs during the Spring Festival, but when the program was finished, it was no longer suitable for the current media environment and had to be postponed.

In February, there were two jobs in Hokkaido and the United States, but due to security and large-scale cancellation of tourists flights and other reasons, the trip was forced to cancel.

The constant frequency of updates is supposed to be a testament to the professionalism of short video bloggers, but the sudden outbreak of the epidemic has made many filming impossible, and the Pre holiday stock has many that are not suitable for broadcast during the epidemic.

Xiao Jiu before the Spring Festival video shot, because not wearing a mask, just sent out on the fans received overwhelming concern and inquiries. "I had to explain it to them one by one for fear of repercussions. I even made a video explaining it later. "

And when Mi Zijun prepared to broadcast the program, the Taiwanese authorities completely banned the export of face masks, "although up to 3,000 gigabytes of material and the team's efforts for nearly a month may have been in vain, we simply can not accept actions that jeopardize cross-strait relations. "

Although pulpo is in Japan, the late members of her studio are all in China, and the co-production partners can not return to work due to the epidemic, making filming and post-production co-operation a difficult matter. In early February, PULPO had to opt for a moratorium.

And similar problems in those who rely more on offline scenes and multi-person offline collaborative work of the MCN body is more prominent.

Kang Kang is the head of Suzhou Xinhuo Network, a small MCN organization that runs douyin generation and incubates Internet celebrities. For nearly a week, Kang Kang has been working hard to get the company back to work.

"We have to get back to work. If we don't get back to work, there's no set, there's no actors, there's no director, there's no way to work offline, there's no way to film it. "

To keep up with the updates, Kang Kang has told the director to plan as many features as possible that don't require multitasking, but that the quality of the content will inevitably decline.

As usual, Kang Kang told interface, they need at least a director, a director, and a cameraman to work with the stars of the show. But now, because of the epidemic, content can only be produced by actors taking selfies at home. "And there are very few people who have this combination of qualities on the doublespeak. "

As head of the company, Kang Kang Now can only hope to complete the resumption of work review as soon as possible, back to normal office.

However, it is not so easy to pass the review, early forms alone to submit six or seven, covering the epidemic prevention and control work plan, resumption of work plan, commitment, material support table, staff table and so on.

Among them, the most difficult to solve is the material problem. Kang Kang said he had stocked up on masks and disinfectant products through various channels before the Spring Festival, but it was not enough. "At the moment, you can only submit the form in advance and wait for the final result of the review. "

And Mi Zijun in order not to affect their own update rhythm, a new "eliminate hoarding" theme, and strive to ensure stable content at home output.

###Missing ad orders

For many short video creators and MCN, the lack of memory may be solved through flexibility and efforts, but the loss of advertising orders is a more serious problem.

According to APP Growing, offline retail, film and travel industries have been hit by the epidemic this Spring Festival, and advertising has been largely suspended. Take the travel industry where octopus is located, for example, the data shows that since January 24, except for ctrip travel, the travel and accommodation industry in the head has basically suspended large-scale advertising. This also means that as an advertising agency from the media and MCN people lost a large number of orders.

"Most of the projects we were working on a year ago have stopped, and even some clients have said we don't have a budget, at this rate, we will lose at least one million per cent in February, " A top-ranked MCN employee at Douyin told interface news.

Kang Kang also said that years ago, they had agreed to a restaurant chain's douyin operation list, but because of the epidemic, the enterprise has been informed to postpone the tender, "We've been booked and the contract is being prepared, but in this case, we'll have to wait. "

There are some co-operation is already in progress, but because the chip is not suitable for the current tone, the enterprise side also proposed to delay co-operation.

In Kang Kang's view, the current market conditions, after the first quarter, a lot of small MCN institutions will not survive.

"It's cool for the first quarter, but after a while, a lot of companies may start to optimize their staff. "

Of course, there is also an option to actively expand new business self-help.

One founder, Xu Husheng, pointed out in an interview with the new list that although advertisers will stop advertising, users still need to buy things. At this time, he advised new media entrepreneurs to immediately expand their sources of income beyond advertising, such as e-commerce sales and knowledge payments. "advertising is not the only revenue model, selling goods, selling classes can be. For example, we have hundreds of Weixin Distribution (merchandise) cooperation, the proportion is not low. "

Kang Kang also said he was trying all possible new businesses, including live streaming, to survive the first quarter. And until the new business brings in revenue, "You have to try to get money, raise money, borrow money. In theory, many brands will invest more in the second quarter to make up for first-quarter losses. If we can get there, we can solve the problem."

###Could live broadcasting be the new way out?

If there was one new media industry that was completely unaffected by the outbreak in February, it was live.

How hot is it on the air? On Feb. 10, Douyin user "whose round three" went to bed live at home and woke up to find that not only did 18.5 million people watch him sleep, but his followers shot up by more than 800,000. And in the round of Sany Bang after the red, Douyin users "big round son" also immediately launched a cat's sleep broadcast, a down, a net reward earned 10,000 yuan.

And those affected by the epidemic of nightclubs, gyms and other industries, also due to the emergence of Cloud Disco, cloud fitness and other live broadcast hot spots, and more or less alleviated the loss of some stores.

On Feb. 10, the day of resuming work, Yang Shuofa, deputy director of a marketing agency in Hangzhou, posted this message on a friend's circle: "If you have an internet celebrity who is bored at home, you can find me to do live broadcast, with a guaranteed bottom line, and enough traffic to make money at home. "

Prior to this, Yang Shuo more energy or will be on-line release and e-commerce with goods. But the epidemic hit the day, offline activities suspended, e-commerce delivery trapped, but gave Yang Shuo a development of the power of live broadcast.

"We had expected this year's live streaming of Douyin to be the talk of the town, " he said. "Red People are stuck at home in February, so we took advantage of this opportunity. "

In Yang Shuo's view, douyin live broadcast can take goods, and can product Xuan, itself is a huge flow pool, after doing a good job will have great benefits. And douyin and other show live is not quite the same, want to do douyin live, short video also catch, and if there is a short video base, do live some more labor-saving.

Therefore, in recent days, many short video organizations have begun to transform live hard to save themselves. Yang Shuo to hear many organizations on the red people put forward a daily broadcast requirements, "broadcast on it, but also require people broadcast three or four hours every day. "

However, live and short video content presentation is very different, like this in order to save the best people without training on the shelf, it is difficult to make real results. "Most of the people who are trained by the short video agencies are used to the kind of regular shooting that has script and direction, " he said. "For live streaming, it's a more casual way to test the talent, emotional intelligence and eloquence of the anchors. If you are not good at it, do it by force, the effect may not be very good,"Yang told interface news.

But on the other hand, he also agreed that this is also a helpless move of many agencies at this stage, "after all, red people have nothing to do but stay at home, so they can still earn some money if they continue to broadcast. Moreover, if the short video + live broadcast model really goes through, then it can also increase the risk tolerance of the whole company. "

In his view, this year's short live video industry market must be upward. After the end of the epidemic, with consumption, travel, catering and other industries recovery, advertising and marketing industry will surely usher in a wave of retaliatory growth. Therefore, the most important thing now is to use this time to think about the next direction of development, and then targeted personnel adjustment and training, waiting for the opportunity to come.

"To put it bluntly, we have to live. Only by living can there be hope. "
